* CIA Traid (Network Security) :                                                                                           =====important question=====
      C - Confidentiality
      I - Integrity
      A - Avaliability
* Autentication : verifying the details of the user
                => something you know(password,email,Two step Verfication,secret things etc...)
                => something you have(OTP,Aadhar,Voter ID,Pan card,License etc.....)
                => something about you(Biometrics,behaviour patterns etc....)
 ====[If you use two factors from the above list that is "2-step verification", If you use all the 3 factors then it is "Multi-step Authentication"]====
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Authorization/Access Control(AC) : permission given to use some datas or files etc.....      
* Confidentiality : 
                => UAC(User Access Control) popup
* Integrity : Originality/Genuinity/Honest
                => It is mostly used in https-443 port.They secure SSL certificate.
                => Whenever you create website or application you have to use integrity to avoid script kiddies or malcious attackers.
* Encryption : conversion of clear text to siffer text(human not understandable form).
* Availability : best example 
                => ATM Machine in the time of Demodilization.
